Your Digest for Tuesday, Apr 09, 2024 08:59 AM

  • Patients can present with elevations of a single type or mixed hyperlipidaemia.
  1. Familial hypercholesterolaemia ( #autosomalDominant ) is one of the commonest causes.
  2. Defects of lipoprotein lipase pathway --> present as medical emergencies due to gross hypertriglyceridaemia (pancreatitis risk)
    3. Pathognomonic physical signs: palmar xanthomata and tuberose xanthomata (over knees and elbows)
    3. Poor response to statins.
    4. Liver transplantation can normalize lipid levels. (?introduces hepatocytes with functioning LDL receptors)

[!TIP] Mnemonic: Fivehundred - Fibrates

[!INFO] Icosapent ethyl
An omega-3 fatty acid, which is also found in fish oil.
It is indicated as an adjunct to maximally tolerated statin therapy. Source

  • I.e Indications for high intensity statin treatment are if the patient has previously has had or is having ASCVD.
    • In which cause, lower LDL to about half the normal values. (100/2 ≈ 55)

⭐Fibrates

  • Increase Lipoprotein lipase activity -> reduce TGLs and increase clearance of VLDL.
  • Increase HDL
  • SE: myositis, nausea, reversible increase in creatinine.
  • DO NOT combine ⭐gemfibrozil with statins
    • liver enzyme elevation - true hepatotoxicity, liver failure are very rare.
      • Rhabdomyolysis / myositis / myopathy is a known side effect (but rare)
    • They can cause new onset diabetes.
  • Novel class of lipid lowering drug.
  • Blocks intestinal absorption of cholesterol by blocking NPC1L1 sterol transporter.
    • Mnemonic: NPCILI looks like vili.
  • Can be combined with statins and PCSK9 inhibitors.
  • Can be used as monotherapy
  • Does not inhibit hepatic cholesterol synthesis or reduce biliary excretion of cholesterol.
  • Can be coadministered with fenofibrate or HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors, but the recommendation is to dose it at least 2 hours before or 4 hours after taking bile acid sequestrants.
  • If LDL > 190 and familia hypercholesterolaemia has been exluded (which must be managed as it's own entity), start high dose (Atorvastatin 40) statin therapy.

  1. The venous drainage of the brain does not have valves to the JVP is directly transmitted to the cerebral veins.
